article.headline: Louisiana Tech 66, New Mexico State 61
article.story: RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Paul Millsap's double-double of 21 points and 14 rebounds helped lead Louisiana Tech to a 66-61 victory over New Mexico State Saturday. Millsap was 8-of-12 from the floor and 5-of-9 from the free throw line. Marcus Elliott added 13 points for the Bulldogs (12-7, 5-1 Western Athletic Conference). Elijah Ingram led New Mexico State (7-9, 3-2) with 15 points. Tyrone Nelson added 14 and Kevin Ford finished with 13. Louisiana Tech led 35-30 at the half. Both teams scored 31 points in the second half, as the Bulldogs withstood a late New Mexico State rally.
